{"id":"1711.01003","submitter":"Xavier Mart\\'inez-Rivera","authors":"Shaun M. Fallat, Xavier Mart\\'inez-Rivera","title":"The quasi principal rank characteristic sequence","comments":"14 pages","journal-ref":"Linear Algebra and its Applications 548 (2018), 42--56","doi":"10.1016/j.laa.2018.02.024","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A minor of a matrix is quasi-principal if it is a principal or an\nalmost-principal minor. The quasi principal rank characteristic sequence\n(qpr-sequence) of an $n\\times n$ symmetric matrix is introduced, which is\ndefined as $q_1 q_2 \\cdots q_n$, where $q_k$ is $\\tt A$, $\\tt S$, or $\\tt N$,\naccording as all, some but not all, or none of its quasi-principal minors of\norder $k$ are nonzero. This sequence extends the principal rank characteristic\nsequences in the literature, which only depend on the principal minors of the\nmatrix. A necessary condition for the attainability of a qpr-sequence is\nestablished. Using probabilistic techniques, a complete characterization of the\nqpr-sequences that are attainable by symmetric matrices over fields of\ncharacteristic $0$ is given.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Nov 2017 02:54:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-19"}
