ELG} \\lesssim 0.94$ ($2.17 \\lesssim z_{S,LAE}\n\\lesssim 4.48$). We show that the algorithmic search is complete at >90% for\nQSO-ELG systems, whereas it falls at 40-60% for QSO-LAE, depending on the\nredshift of the source. Upon confirmation of the lensing nature of the systems,\nthis sample may quadruple the number of known QSOs acting as strong lenses. We\nhave determined the completeness of our search, which allows future studies to\ncompute lensing probabilities of galaxies by QSOs and differentiate between\ndifferent QSO models. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Nov 2017 14:32:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Mar 2019 10:57:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-13"}
